Hi @tb2186,

Thank you for raising this issue! Subnet outputs are now fully supported as of **release [v0.14.0](https://github.com/Azure/terraform-azurerm-avm-res-network-virtualnetwork/releases/tag/v0.14.0)** and later.

## Available Subnet Outputs

The module provides comprehensive subnet information through the `subnets` output, which includes all subnet details from the subnet module:

- `address_prefixes` - The address prefixes of the subnet (works for both static and IPAM subnets)
- `name` - The resource name of the subnet
- `resource_id` - The resource ID of the subnet
- `resource` - All attributes of the subnet resource

## How to Access Subnet Outputs

```terraform
module "vnet" {
  source = "Azure/avm-res-network-virtualnetwork/azurerm"
  version = "~> 0.14"

  name          = "my-vnet"
  location      = "East US"
  parent_id     = azurerm_resource_group.example.id
  address_space = ["10.0.0.0/16"]

  subnets = {
    "web" = {
      name             = "web-subnet"
      address_prefixes = ["10.0.1.0/24"]
    }
    "app" = {
      name             = "app-subnet"
      address_prefixes = ["10.0.2.0/24"]
    }
  }
}

# Access specific subnet outputs
output "web_subnet_id" {
  description = "Resource ID of the web subnet"
  value       = module.vnet.subnets["web"].resource_id
}

output "web_subnet_address_prefixes" {
  description = "Address prefixes of the web subnet"
  value       = module.vnet.subnets["web"].address_prefixes
}

# Access all subnet resource IDs
output "all_subnet_ids" {
  description = "Resource IDs of all subnets"
  value = {
    for name, subnet in module.vnet.subnets : name => subnet.resource_id
  }
}

# Access complete subnet information
output "subnet_details" {
  description = "Complete subnet information"
  value       = module.vnet.subnets
}
```
## IPAM Subnet Support
The outputs work seamlessly with both traditional and IPAM-allocated subnets:
```terraform
# For IPAM subnets, address_prefixes shows dynamically allocated ranges
output "ipam_subnet_allocated_prefixes" {
  description = "Dynamically allocated prefixes from IPAM pool"
  value       = module.vnet.subnets["ipam_subnet"].address_prefixes
}
```
> [!NOTE]
> The subnet outputs provide consistent access to all subnet information regardless of whether subnets use traditional static addressing or dynamic IPAM allocation.

If you have any specific subnet output requirements not covered above, please feel free to raise a new issue with details about what additional outputs would be helpful!

