The AzAPI provider will do duplicate detection on lists of objects than have a `name` property, treating them like maps. I will put forward a feature request to extend the "key" values to other properties.

### Long term potential solution

```hcl
resource "azapi_resource" "subnet" {
  # other stuff
  body = {
    properties = {
      serviceEndpoints = [
        {
          service = "Microsoft.Web"
        },
        {
          service = "Microsoft.KeyVault"
        }
      ]
    }
  }

  # The below would tell the provider to treat this list as a map,
  # ensuring that the provided values were present, but not re-ordering/removing
  # others.
  list_unique_id_property = {
    "properties.ServiceEndpoints": "service"
  }
}
```

