@timja, rebased my branch onto your `fix-ip-address-allocation` tip, so `main.tf`, `modules/subnet/ipam.tf`, `modules/subnet/variables.tf` and the examples are identical to yours now. The only delta is one validation block in root `variables.tf` that catches `ipam_pools` entries with neither `number_of_ip_addresses` nor `prefix_length` set. Without it, the plan blows up inside `main.tf` when it tries to compute from a null prefix length.

```hcl
validation {
  condition = alltrue([
    for ipam_pool in var.ipam_pools != null ? var.ipam_pools : [] : ipam_pool.number_of_ip_addresses != null || ipam_pool.prefix_length != null
  ]) || var.ipam_pools == null
  error_message = "Each IPAM pool entry must specify either number_of_ip_addresses or prefix_length."
}
```

PR against your branch: timja/terraform-azurerm-avm-res-network-virtualnetwork#1

Heads up on a pre-existing gap, not from this work: the "Only one IPv4 pool" and "Only one IPv6 pool" validations classify pools by `prefix_length`. With `prefix_length` now optional, a pool specified only by `number_of_ip_addresses` slips past both at plan time. Azure rejects it server side so it is not critical, just worth knowing.

